%N A225787 Least prime number p such that p*triangular(n) is a triangular number, or 0 if no such p exists.
%H A225787 Robert Israel, <a href="/A225787/b225787.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%F A225787 a(n) <= n^2 + n + 2.  For n>0, a(n) <= n^2 + n + 1.
%e A225787 Least prime p such that triangular(3)*p is a triangular number is p=11, so a(3) = 11.
%p A225787 f:= proc(n) local m,y,S;
%p A225787   m:= 4*n*(n+1);
%p A225787   S:= map(t -> rhs(op(t)), [msolve(y^2-1,m)]);
%p A225787   S:= select(isprime, map(t -> (t^2-1)/m, S));
%p A225787   if S = [] then 0 else min(S) fi
%p A225787 end proc:
%p A225787 f(0):= 2:
%p A225787 map(f, [$0..100]); # _Robert Israel_, Nov 04 2025
